BUDDING act Akintomide Makinde aka Liltommy has expressed what music means to him in a recent chat. The indie artist made the revelation in a chat with The Nation while speaking about his musical journey and his career. He said, “Music to me is my best means of communication. It’s a universal language that enables me to communicate with anybody regardless of where you come from. What I have for music is more than a calling, because it’s my passion and legacy. I enjoy making people enjoy music” Continuing, he said, “I’ve been doing music professionally for seven years since 2015 when I debuted my official single ‘Highray’ featuring Base10 and AshFlames with an official video to compliment it.”   One year after viral burial Obi Cubana eulogises mom     Fela, Keith Richards inspired my career – Highlife Soes     There’s still hope for Nigeria – Davido   Liltommy just released a ten-track extended play (EP) entitled ‘African Kushking’ that features Base10, AshFlames, KoladeBless, and Timi Kupo. According to the young talented act, the project was inspired by God and real-life situations. In his words, “It is inspired by realities happening around us every day and the EP relates with every sphere of our daily lives; it’s enjoyable regardless of what mood or location you find yourself; whether in church or a club.”